English: Third, Islamism has historic and philosophic ties to MarxismLeninism. Sayyid Qutb, the Egyptian Islamist thinker, accepted the Marxist notion of stages of history, only adding an Islamic postscript to them he predicted that an eternal Islamic era would come after the collapse of capitalism and Communism. Ali Shariati , the key intellectual behind the Iranian revolution of 197879, translated Franz Fanon, Che Guevara, and JeanPaul Sartre into Persian. More broadly, the Iranian analyst Azar Nafisi observes that Islamism takes its language, goals, and aspirations as much from the crassest forms of Marxism as it does from religion.
